		-
			-
				Chapter 20 - The Victory: Verse 1
			-
				-
					Now behold - from one end of existence to the other, did all Angaia make merry
					with sister and with brother, and in this new destiny, where life reigned
					eternally, and the doom of death descended never, all Angaia trembled as they
					entered Xyro together!
				-
			-
				Chapter 20 - The Victory: Verse 2
			-
				-
					Yea behold, the Ace had done as foretold, and all mankind and all the beasts,
					from the greatest to the least, held Kaeon in ultimate esteem, for by it had
					they been redeemed!
				-
		-
			Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare
		-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 1
			-
				-
					And with the end of their mission, the Ace retired to their work's fruition,
					and took a fellow's station, to dwell among redeemed creation.
				-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 2
			-
				-
					Yet despite the people's stubborn efforts to deify their teacher, the Ace
					sought no false worship or adoring preachers, but here and there they came to
					sit, and taught to any who would listen, the science of wisdom and touch of
					wit, and many a mind were thus christened.
				-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 3
			-
				-
					And the Ace planted their staff a seed, and it became a towering tree, whose
					stature could not help but overwhelm, as its branches branched into and over
					many other realms.
				-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 4
			-
				-
					Thus concluded the epic of humanity, giving closure to the story of history, as
					Angaia - one and all, went to reign in Xyro's halls.
				-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 5
			-
				-
					BEHOLD - THE VICTOR O'ER ANGAIA'S CRIES, IS KAEON AND ITS ACE OF A-XY!
				-
			-
				Chapter 21 - The End of the Nightmare: Verse 6
